Package: yappr
Type: Package
Title: Hebrew NLP in R via YAP, in the 'quanteda' Workflow
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Almog",
                  family = "Simchon",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "almogsi@post.bgu.ac.il")
Description: An R client for YAP (Yet Another Parser), the open-source
    morphological analyzer, disambiguator, and dependency parser for Hebrew
    developed by the ONLP Lab (<https://github.com/OnlpLab/yap>). The package
    talks to a local YAP server over loopback HTTP and exposes a
    'spacyr'-style tidy data frame that plugs directly into the 'quanteda'
    ecosystem via 'as.tokens()'. Includes a one-shot Hebrew-aware DFM builder
    that lemmatizes, filters by part of speech, strips punctuation, and
    removes Hebrew stopwords.
